  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to determine the impact of primary care referrals to community
      physical activity programs for overweight and obese youth aged 6-18 years on objectively
      measured physical activity and cardiorespiratory fitness, as well as other cardiovascular
      health indicators. We hypothesize that physical activity referrals will result in higher
      levels of physical activity and fitness.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
